summary: The document is a 'SECRET' deferred tele-pouch related to the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992. It examines the absence of documented contacts between members of the Vlaamse Militanten Orde (VMO) and American citizens from 1968 to 1970 and indicates resistance against compiling a report on this matter for the House of Representatives Committee.
key_findings: The document is part of the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
It highlights a gap in information regarding interactions between VMO members and American citizens during 1968-1970.
There is noted opposition to the creation of a report on the VMO for the House of Representatives Committee.
keywords: President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992
